The cotangent of an angle is defined as the ratio of the cosine of the angle to the sine of the angle:

$$\cot \theta = \frac{\cos \theta}{\sin \theta}$$

Evaluating this at  $\theta = 90^\circ$, we have:

$$\cot 90^\circ = \frac{\cos 90^\circ}{\sin 90^\circ}$$

Recall that $\cos 90^\circ = 0$ and $\sin 90^\circ = 1$.  Therefore:

$$\cot 90^\circ = \frac{0}{1} = 0$$



\begin{equation*}
\cot 90^\circ = \boxed{0}
\end{equation*}

